  "url": "sec_force-and-potential-energy.html",
  "type": "Section",
  "number": "4.14",
  "title": "Force and Potential Energy",
  "body": " Force and Potential Energy  Discussing the relationship between force and potential energy.   Force and Potential Energy   Potential energy and the corresponding conservative force are related (in one dimension, ) by .     Activity: Practice Diagram  Below is a potential energy diagram for some system.   A potential energy diagram.   A graph of U vs. x that starts near 4 J, decreases to 1 J at x = 4 m and then rises to around 6 J.    What property of the graph can you use to identify the force that this particle experiences? Explain your reasoning.    At what position(s) is the force on the particle zero?    "
